<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="813" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="55.[1391,2602,2601,3458]" pageId="55" pageNumber="813">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1393,1745,3307,3340]" pageId="55" pageNumber="813">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Burmese Pipistrelle is known only from the holotype, collected in 1915. Nothing is known of its ecology and threats. Further sampling is needed.
</paragraph>
